hase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 477, \"output\": 873, \"cacheRead\": 56320, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 57670, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1777692423453, \"responseId\": \"resp_02c2857ea90408210169f56f080e7481969102239cb0ecc418\"}}\n6296:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Considering memory utilization**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how after catch and restore, the direct test will use `MemoryUtil.directBuffer`. However, the system initializes normally with MemoryUtil, but it can't get the long and int constructor when DIRECT is null, which leads to an Unsupported catch. I need to install the long and long constructor. If I invoke MemoryUtil.directBuffer with Long and Integer (Integer.TYPE normal), it should succeed since we've tested it earlier. Everything seems positive so far!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_02c2857ea90408210169f56f09400481968711bb376ab53f6e\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp9W8StbmW-PF9wXOPC988fsEz30hrBcDTvTjCbeivztwPus26qksRg2ZMAq07hdmfMmCSW6bNW29AyDU35zA4TALgrVWkXcQ8JwHc0M2-IiI7GtfvF5iI_v54AIoclkFzA-6bgkZKU6XKn3mDve_L-k-qmOvVpTwZQg4L62px6C2AvX8S9RLshCT-1TC1H-MXX9TTtqDw8ySrvH3cef5Ttu3TZkDi7-hQpnJwbGgrQy83TYQxBC_gBhg7-4nMYdRXCeCwerlqyK6qJeRfMZlZ9MIElCP5hNivMfEkNAEenGjS5AMHd5gRQA6SWqJksfjAcbmPk6QaQ5JHAjlxqVQIK2Vas5BpV1D_lXACV2VEZsAvdsDXkpXUK1FEYl05aHAnrcxZVhkoyQB_8wz0d1G4UGLFeaFt1Q45eAj4hvIFbaXGnTvi1jbn4XVPt1_zR02Hs1FJUf-KFVeDxLl6I-Pm6UhR8giu1OKYF4-C6SLnK6V5GikvzR6DvBqVKZf_ADN0BjvAOhgtsDfZNM_sBbYSfzd6-qQyo2PMVmqRDyOxBTSBD_9znJMOPrmkFzQXKxh6TYMaagfT1tRGUotLHe7RKFS65tBVqGx8kdvnbIiNVOJ-6u_xuDTJb_Xd-k5JWab_42gUcx57zD5L1jHUZczdyn63RUcQDMHHjmVB2UYWcKZ1ea2XBl754Ha3pCZOr-WG671h0RLDoxu_7K13tkq1y7Qcp47