type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Simplifying coverage for directBuffer**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about simplifying by not installing a compatible constructor, especially since it’s causing an error anyway. Maybe we could try using directBuffer that accepts Unsupported or Error? However, if the DIRECT_BUFFER_CONSTRUCTOR is null— which seems common in modern setups— directBuffer would throw Unsupported before line 162, so the site isn’t fully covered. Do we really need new coverage? It might be beneficial to preserve the previous coverage for directBuffer, but it may not be necessary either. Final coverage could include both options.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_xmxdbHc6PUkj6eYLP3pht9ti|fc_02c2857ea90408210169f56f2822fc8196a92cccdf63d6eb1d\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.apache.arrow/arrow-memory-core/7.0.0/src/test/java/org_apache_arrow/arrow_memory_core/MemoryUtilTest.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"            ByteBuffer buffer = directBuffer(address, 8);\\n\\n            assertThat(buffer.isDirect()).isTrue();\\n            assertThat(buffer.capacity()).isEqualTo(8);\\n            assertThat(MemoryUtil.getByteBufferAddress(buffer)).isEqualTo(address);\\n\\n            buffer.put(0, (byte) 42);\\n            assertThat(MemoryUtil.UNSAFE.getByte(address)).isEqualTo((byte) 42);\\n\\n            MemoryUtil.UNSAFE.putByte(address + 1, (byte) 7);\\n            assertThat(buffer.get(1)).isEqualTo((byte) 7);\\n\", \"newText\": \"            ByteBuffer buffer = directBufferOrNull(address, 8);\\n\\n            if (buffer == null) {\\n                ByteBuffer ordinaryDirectBuffer = ByteBuffer.allocateDirect(1);\\n                assertThat(MemoryUtil.getByteBufferAddress(ordinaryDirectBuffer)).isNotZero();\\n            } else {\\n                assertThat(buffer.isDirect()).isTrue();\\n                assertThat(buffer.capacity()).isEqualTo(8);\\n                assertThat(MemoryUtil.getByteBufferAddress(buffer)).isEqualTo(address);\\n\\n                buffer.put(0, (byte) 42);\\n                assertThat(MemoryUtil.UNSAFE.getByte(address)).isEqualTo((byte) 42);\\n\\n                MemoryUtil.UNSAFE.putByte(address + 1, (byte) 7);\\n                assertThat(buffer.get(1)).isEqualTo((byte) 7);\\n            }\\n\"}, {\"oldText\": \"    private static ByteBuffer directBuffer(long address, int capacity) throws ReflectiveOperationException {\\n        try {\\n            return MemoryUtil.directBuffer(address, capacity);\\n        } catch (UnsupportedOperationException unsupported) {\\n            assertThat(unsupported).hasMessageContaining(\\\"DirectByteBuffer.<init>(long, int) not available\\\");\\n            installCompatibleDirectBufferConstructor();\\n            return MemoryUtil.directBuffer(address, capacity);\\n        }\\n    }\\n\", \"newText\": \"    private static ByteBuffer directBufferOrNull(long address, int capacity) throws ReflectiveOperationException {\\n        try {\\n            return MemoryUtil.directBuffer(address, capacity);\\n        } catch (UnsupportedOperationException unsupported) {\\n            assertThat(unsupported).hasMessageContaining(\\\"DirectByteBuffer.<init>(long, int) not available\\\");\\n            installCompatibleDirectBufferConstructor();\\n            try {\\n                return MemoryUtil.directBuffer(address, capacity);\\n            } catch (Error error) {\\n                assertThat(causeOfType(error, IllegalArgumentException.class)).isNotNull();\\n                return null;\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\\n\"}]}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 6165, \"output\": 1549, \"cacheRead\": 49152, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 56866, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777692441157, \"responseId\": \"resp_02c2857ea90408210169f56f1a2fb08196bb8141e880add3a7\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_xmxdbHc6PUkj6eYLP3pht9ti|fc_02c2857ea90408210169f56f2822fc8196a92cccdf63d6eb1d\", \"toolName\": \"edit\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Successfully replaced 2 block(s) in tests/src/org.apache.arrow/arrow-memory-core/7.0.0/src/test/java/org_apache_arrow/arrow_memory_core/MemoryUtilTest.java.\"}], \"details\": {\"diff\": \"     ...\\n  33         long address = MemoryUtil.UNSAFE.allocateMemory(8);\\n  34         try {\\n  35             MemoryUtil.UNSAFE.setMemory(address, 8, (byte) 0);\\n  36 \\n- 37             ByteBuffer buffer = directBuffer(address, 8);\\n+ 37             ByteBuffer buffer = directBufferOrNull(address, 8);\\n  38 \\n- 39             assertThat(buffer.isDirect()).isTrue();\\n- 40             assertThat(buffer.capacity()).isEqualTo(8);\\n- 41             assertThat(MemoryUtil.getByteBufferAddress(buffer)).isEqualTo(address);\\n+ 39             if (buffer == null) {\\n+ 40                 ByteBuffer ordinaryDirectBuffer = ByteBuffer.allocateDirect(1);\\n+ 41                 assertThat(MemoryUtil.getByteBufferAddress(ordinaryDirectBuffer)).isNotZero();\\n+ 42             } else {\\n+ 43                 assertThat(buffer.isDirect()).isTrue();\\n+ 44                 assertThat(buffer.capacity()).isEqualTo(8);\\n+ 45                 assertThat(MemoryUtil.getByteBufferAddress(buffer)).isEqualTo(address);\\n  42 \\n- 43             buffer.put(0, (byte) 42);\\n- 44             assertThat(MemoryUtil.UNSAFE.getByte(address)).isEqualTo((byte) 42);\\n+ 47                 buffer.put(0, (byte) 42);\\n+ 48                 assertThat(MemoryUtil.UNSAFE.getByte(address)).isEqualTo((byte) 42);\\n  45 \\n- 46             MemoryUtil.UNSAFE.putByte(address + 1, (byte) 7);\\n- 47             assertThat(buffer.get(1)).isEqualTo((byte) 7);\\n+ 50                 MemoryUtil.UNSAFE.putByte(address + 1, (byte) 7);\\n+ 51                 assertThat(buffer.get(1)).isEqualTo((byte) 7);\\n+ 52             }\\n  48         } finally {\\n  49             MemoryUtil.UNSAFE.freeMemory(address);\\n  50         }\\n  51     }\\n     ...\\n 100         }\\n 101         throw new IllegalStateException(\\\"Unable to locate arrow-memory-core on the test class path\\\");\\n 102     }\\n 103 \\n-104     private static ByteBuffer directBuffer(long address, int capacity) throws ReflectiveOperationException {\\n+109     private static ByteBuffer directBufferOrNull(long address, int capacity) throws ReflectiveOperationException {\\n 105         try {\\n 106             return MemoryUtil.directBuffer(address, capacity);\\n 107         } catch (UnsupportedOperationException unsupported) {\\n 108             assertThat(unsupported).hasMessageContaining(\\\"DirectByteBuffer.<init>(long, int) not available\\\");\\n 109             installCompatibleDirectBufferConstructor();\\n-110             return MemoryUtil.directBuffer(address, capacity);\\n+115             try {\\n+116                 return MemoryUtil.directBuffer(address, capacity);\\n+117             } catch (Error error) {\\n+118                 assertThat(causeOfType(error, IllegalArgumentException.class)).isNotNull();\\n+119                 return null;\\n+120             }\\n 111         }\\n 112     }\\n 113 \\n 114     private static void installCompatibleDirectBufferConstructor() throws ReflectiveOperationException {\\n     ...\", \"firstChangedLine\": 37}, \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777692459278}]}\n6474:[thinking] I'm thinking about how under Native Image, URLClassLoader dynamic loading isn't supported. There's a chance that locating the classpath might fail before an error occurs. I wonder if we should use a try block for the arrowMemoryCoreJarUrl. If it fails due to the missing classpath, should we really skip it? But then, this path seems like it would only improve coverage in the JVM agent, not necessarily for native test coverage. Interesting dilemma!\n6484:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Considering classpath issues**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how under Native Image, URLClassLoader dynamic loading isn't supported. There's a chance that locating the classpath might fail before an error occurs. I wonder if we should use a try block for the arrowMemoryCoreJarUrl. If it fails due to the missing classpath, should we really skip it? But then, this path seems like it would only improve coverage in the JVM agent, not necessarily for native test coverage. Interesting dilemma!\\n\\n**Considering naming conventions**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether “directBufferWraps…” is a suitable name, especially if the buffer is null. I wonder if renaming it to “directBufferConstructorPathsAreExercised” might be more descriptive. On the other hand, maybe it’s not necessary to change it. I’m also pondering if it makes sense to run a test with this naming decision. There’s a lot to weigh here!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_02c2857ea90408210169f56f2ccfd88196be65f837fa841845\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp9W88wT0e7YRE5rAIowdf2d-1r-vu-ioBMxAJ5feJA9iw5-cbsor1Ld9N9xPcfhLHCYOBE3Hpy7VsbHXy5YLiN86ZZAIDXkCrvZkhiB7FLLfHrt9BxpH30AAhCF_3BG6qWmpQNyakpuDDqJflgaqkOvFRHL7Ua8jSD2u8-PrScnmzxdB6PtNceMgY4FCpKTq5kRkviTZ-t-ajM65KiTYZHVxc-7Z7WSCw7p8mSgo2mF2N1blJoNClcw7CzWVV9ukU-RfqNHndn748_zqS4rvB8-IxL6Tgd1uZJy1vFG_B3xbWTj0YCBLEImrunyMLHBlBKEVDT-siEVlDJccqETS7GpwWXSXvohYcvxTsL-f6rwHuMqM3Lbu2xAqD7i87UkYMNaQXRrz15yU4sOQiqYMfgDaDJKzLUVfRliKTlrLb2WALRFI_7WB5sCmoF7lk1BJSAcASjDGoSO0Nwdwd3eaqK5o_WgNqap8pGcnDBsgfmMh4jdWQrd9D_JqxDSHrgXsJ9Y3MXIilBR7HgKZw80LErRrqwPlig4AlMmaAbDbO2OllR7KDp2iMk1SyKXJuTwfeTn_Sd8RbQpcLHe4AxeZdS9MgAIfAKbZaSamh4Ot5w_tRTPdYIPzVw4_TJMrQtAvrcRu4_Uvvpdco3nVy553cMl1mYs0mY51_7pHZr9oQf4fLBehbJhh2q5jwQfzZkyl6mga43Enobi-fREyd8CtFVADMRsXomIIvexBkXV3cch_CSM0JUbsHyz-WwpP-zbbZUPUMPhyARTcj2SMItrOmx4w4YWYBpUP5uHaXzz