 JVM agent, not necessarily for native test coverage. Interesting dilemma!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering naming conventions**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about whether “directBufferWraps…” is a suitable name, especially if the buffer is null. I wonder if renaming it to “directBufferConstructorPathsAreExercised” might be more descriptive. On the other hand, maybe it’s not necessary to change it. I’m also pondering if it makes sense to run a test with this naming decision. There’s a lot to weigh here!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_dkaripFh0cGAwdW8FrS1fsiP|fc_02c2857ea90408210169f56f3cafc0819697f363ba8edcd952\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.apache.arrow/arrow-memory-core/7.0.0/src/test/java/org_apache_arrow/arrow_memory_core/MemoryUtilTest.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"    private static URL arrowMemoryCoreJarUrl() throws Exception {\\n        URL resource = MemoryUtilTest.class.getClassLoader().getResource(MEMORY_UTIL_CLASS_RESOURCE);\\n\", \"newText\": \"    private static URL arrowMemoryCoreJarUrl() throws Exception {\\n        URL codeSource = MemoryUtil.class.getProtectionDomain().getCodeSource().getLocation();\\n        if (codeSource != null) {\\n            return codeSource;\\n        }\\n\\n        URL resource = MemoryUtilTest.class.getClassLoader().getResource(MEMORY_UTIL_CLASS_RESOURCE);\\n\"}]}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 2132, \"output\": 1209, \"cacheRead\": 54784, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 58125, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777692459282, \"responseId\": \"resp_02c2857ea90408210169f56f2bf63c8196a9d94a38acce3099\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_dkaripFh0cGAwdW8FrS1fsiP|fc_02c2857ea90408210169f56f3cafc0819697f363ba8edcd952\", \"too