e failing output back to the agent, clears agent context after each class attempt sequence, treats the phase as successful once any dynamic-access call site becomes covered, enforces per-class prompt-attempt limits, and fails the generation if the dynamic-access report disappears mid-phase.\\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:12:  - `_generate_dynamic_access_report(...)`: runs `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` and loads parsed report data from `dynamic-access-coverage.json`.\\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:21:2. **Coverage improvement** — increase dynamic-access coverage of\\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:33:   dynamic-access coverage of already-supported libraries.\\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:53:| **Dynamic-access report** | JSON written by Gradle task `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` to `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`, listing classes and per-class call sites that require dynamic-access metadata, marked covered/uncovered. |\\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:76:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` — only honored by dynamic-access\\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:77:  strategies; see [dynamic-access-workflow.md](dynamic-access-workflow.md).\\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:89:  `dynamic-access-iteration`).\\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:138:- [Dynamic access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) — guided test\\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:139:  generation driven by the dynamic-access coverage report.\\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:149:  additional tests to improve dynamic-access coverage on an existing library\\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:200:| `dynamic_access_iterative` | [dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py](../ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py) | Coverage-driven loop using the dynamic-access report; targets uncovered call sites. |\\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:201:| `optimistic_dynamic_access` | [optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py](../ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py) | Variant of dynamic-access that primes coverage from source analysis. |\\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:238:| `dynamic_access_report` | Parse `dynamic-access-coverage.json`, compute deltas, format prompts. |\\n./forge/docs/architecture.md:270:  recovery, dynamic-access iteration, javac/java-run failure prompts).\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version me